b2bpl.graph
Class AbstractVertex<V extends AbstractVertex<V,E>,E extends AbstractEdge<V,E>>

java.lang.Object
  b2bpl.graph.AbstractVertex<V,E>
Type Parameters:
V - A type parameter representing the concrete vertex to be used as a basic block in the control flow graph.
E - A type parameter representing the concrete edge to be used in the control flow graph.
Direct Known Subclasses:
BasicBlock, BasicBlock
public abstract class AbstractVertex<V extends AbstractVertex<V,E>,E extends AbstractEdge<V,E>>
extends java.lang.Object

Abstract class representing a vertex in a control flow graph.

A vertex is basically characterized by a set of ingoing and outgoing edges which are instances of the AbstractEdge class.

Author:
Ovidio Mallo
See Also:
AbstractEdge, AbstractFlowGraph
